{"name": "np-config", "metadata": {"name": "np-config", "version": "0.4.34", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["kazoo", "pyyaml", "typing-extensions", "requests", "backports-cached-property", "singledispatch", "types-singledispatch", "platformdirs"], "summary": "Config fetching from file or Zookeeper - with local backup - repackaging code from AIBS mpeconfig.", "upload_time": 1719426229}, "documentation": ["# np_config\n\n\n### *For use on internal Allen Institute network*\n\n## Usage\n\nFetch configs from ZooKeeper nodes or .yaml/.json files:\n\n```python\nimport np_config\n\nzk_config: dict[str, str | int] = np_config.from_zk('/rigs/NP.1')\n\nfile_config: dict[str, Any] = np_config.from_file('local_config.yaml')\n\n```\n\n\nIf running on a machine attached to a Mindscope Neuropixels rig (`NP.0`, ..., `NP.3`), get rig-specific config info with:\n\n```python\nrig = np_config.Rig()\n\nname: str = rig.id                            # \"NP.1\"\nindex: int = rig.idx                          # 1\n\nacquisition_pc_hostname: str = rig.acq        # \"W10DT713843\"\nconfig: dict[str, str | int] = rig.config     # specific to NP.1\npaths: dict[str, pathlib.Path] = rig.paths    # using values from rig.config\n```\n\n\n\nIf not running on a rig-attached machine, get the config for a particular rig by supplying rig-index as an `int` to `Rig`:\n\n```python\nnp1 = np_config.Rig(1)\n\nnp1_mvr_data_root: pathlib.Path = np.paths['MVR']\n```\n\n\n***\n\n\n- the Mindscope ZooKeeper server is at `eng-mindscope:2181`\n- configs can be added via ZooNavigator webview:\n  [http://eng-mindscope:8081](http://eng-mindscope:8081)\n- or more conveniently, via an extension for VSCode such as [gaoliang.visual-zookeeper](https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=gaoliang.visual-zookeeper)\n\n## Development\nInitialize for local development\n\n```bash\npoetry install --with dev\n```\n\nRun the tests\n\n```bash\npoetry run pytest\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "np_config.utils", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "np_config.utils.merge", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "base", "type": {"name": "MutableMappingType", "xref": {"fqname": "MutableMappingType", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "update", "type": {"name": "Mapping", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Mapping", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "MutableMappingType", "xref": {"fqname": "MutableMappingType", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Utility function to do a deep merge on dictionaries. `base` will be modified, so deep\ncopy first if the original needs to be preserved. This is a recursive function, so\nit merges nested dicts. If a value isn't a dict in both `base` and `update` the\nvalues won't be merged: the value from `update` will override that of `base`.\n\nFrom mpeconfig.\n\n```pycon\n>>> merge({0: {'a': False}, 1: False}, {0: {'a': True, 'b': True}, 1: True})\n{0: {'a': True, 'b': True}, 1: True}\n```\n"]}, {"name": "np_config.utils.local_to_unc", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "host", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "path", "type": {"name": "str | pathlib.Path", "xref": null, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "pathlib.Path", "xref": {"fqname": "pathlib.Path", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Generate a UNC path (for Windows) from host + local path.\n\n```pycon\n>>> local_to_unc(\"W10DT713843\", pathlib.Path(\"C:\\ProgramData\\AIBS_MPE\\MVR\\data\")).as_posix()\n'//W10DT713843/C/ProgramData/AIBS_MPE/MVR/data'\n```\n\n```pycon\n>>> local_to_unc(\"W10DT713843\", \"C$/ProgramData/AIBS_MPE/MVR/data\").as_posix()\n'//W10DT713843/C$/ProgramData/AIBS_MPE/MVR/data'\n```\n"]}, {"name": "np_config.utils.unc_to_local", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "path", "type": {"name": "str | pathlib.Path", "xref": null, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "pathlib.Path", "xref": {"fqname": "pathlib.Path", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Try to convert UNC path with drive letter to local path (for Windows).\n\n```pycon\n>>> unc_to_local(\"//W10DT713843/C/ProgramData/AIBS_MPE/MVR/data\").as_posix()\n'C:/ProgramData/AIBS_MPE/MVR/data'\n```\n\nPath with no drive letter will raise an error:\n\\>>> unc_to_local(\"//w10dtsm18306/neuropixels_data\")\nTraceback (most recent call last):\n\n> ...\n\nValueError: UNC path points to a host + share name (not host + drive letter): insufficient information to construct a local path from //w10dtsm18306/neuropixels_data\n"]}, {"name": "np_config.utils.normalize_path", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "path", "type": {"name": "str | pathlib.Path", "xref": null, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "pathlib.Path", "xref": {"fqname": "pathlib.Path", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Normalize a path to a pathlib.Path object, starting with `//` if a network path.\n\n```pycon\n>>> normalize_path(\"\\W10DT713843\\c/ProgramData/AIBS_MPE/MVR/data\").as_posix()\n'//W10DT713843/c/ProgramData/AIBS_MPE/MVR/data'\n```\n"]}, {"name": "np_config.utils.local_or_unc_path", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "host", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "path", "type": {"name": "str | pathlib.Path", "xref": null, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "pathlib.Path", "xref": {"fqname": "pathlib.Path", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Get a path that works from a location on the host computer. \n\n- converts a UNC path to a local path if running on the host computer specified in the\nUNC path.\n- converts a local path to a UNC path if running on a different computer."]}, {"name": "np_config.utils.rig_idx", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "id", "type": {"name": "str | None", "xref": null, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "Literal[0, 1, 2, 3, 4] | None", "xref": null, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Convert rig ID (`'NP.1'`) to valid rig index (`1`).\n\n```pycon\n>>> rig_idx('NP.1')\n1\n>>> rig_idx('NP1')\n1\n```\n\nAlso accepts bad input, if index is valid:\n\\>>> rig_idx('1')\n1\n\\>>> rig_idx(1)\n1\n"]}, {"name": "np_config.utils.normalize_time", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "t", "type": {"name": "str | float | int | datetime.datetime", "xref": null, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["A standard time format matching platform JSON files.\n\n```pycon\n>>> normalize_time(datetime.datetime(2023, 2, 14, 13, 30, 00))\n'20230214133000'\n>>> normalize_time(1676410200.0)\n'20230214133000'\n>>> normalize_time(1676410200)\n'20230214133000'\n>>> normalize_time('1676410200.0')\n'20230214133000'\n>>> normalize_time('1676410200')\n'20230214133000'\n>>> normalize_time('2023-02-14T13:30:00')\n'20230214133000'\n```\n"]}, {"name": "np_config.utils._", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "t", "type": {"name": "datetime.datetime", "xref": {"fqname": "datetime.datetime", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "np_config.utils._", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "t", "type": {"name": "float", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.float", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "np_config.utils._", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "t", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "np_config.utils._", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "t", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "np_config.utils.logger", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "np_config.utils.HOSTNAME", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "np_config.utils.MutableMappingType", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "np_config.utils.PLATFORM_JSON_TIME_FMT", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "np_config.rigs", "documentation": ["Access to rig computer hostnames and rig-wide ZooKeeper configs.\n\n\\::\n\\### When running on a rig-attached computer\n\nAIBS MPE computer and rig IDs:\n\\>>> COMP_ID, get_rig_id(), get_rig_idx() # doctest: +SKIP\n'NP.1-Acq', 'NP.1', 1\n\n\\### For specific rigs\n\nAIBS MPE rig ID:\n\\>>> Rig(1).id\n'NP.1'\n\nHostnames for each rig computer \\[Sync, Mon, Acq, Stim\\]:\n\\>>> Rig(1).Acq\n'W10DT713843'\n\nPaths for specific apps running on a rig:\n\\>>> Rig(1).paths['MVR'].as_posix()\n'//W10DTSM112721/c\\$/ProgramData/AIBS_MPE/mvr/data'\n\nConfig dict for a particular rig, fetched from ZooKeeper /rigs/NP.\\<idx>:\n\\>>> Rig(1).config['pretest_mouse']\n599657\n\nWhen running on a rig, its NP-index is obtained from an env var, making the current rig's\nproperties available by default:\n\\>>> Rig().Acq # doctest: +SKIP\n'W10DT713843'\n\nIf app is running on the local computer, its path is represented as a local path:\n\\>>> Rig().paths['Sync'] # doctest: +SKIP\nWindowsPath('C:/ProgramData/AIBS_MPE/sync/data')\n\n...otherwise, as a network path:\n\\>>> Rig().paths['Stim'] # doctest: +SKIP\nWindowsPath('//W10DT713942/c\\$/ProgramData/AIBS_MPE/camstim/data')\n"], "functions": [{"name": "np_config.rigs.get_mpe_computer_ids", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "key", "type": {"name": "Literal['comp_ids', 'rig_ids', 'cluster_ids'] | None", "xref": null, "params": null}, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "dict", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.dict", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "Any", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Any", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": ["Get a mapping of computer/rig/cluster IDs and their corresponding information."]}, {"name": "np_config.rigs.get_id_to_comp_ids", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "dict", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.dict", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "list", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.list", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}]}, "documentation": ["make mappings for easier lookup"]}, {"name": "np_config.rigs.get_comp_id_to_hostname", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "dict", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.dict", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "np_config.rigs.get_hostname_to_comp_id", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "dict", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.dict", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "np_config.rigs.get_rig_id_to_hostnames", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "dict", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.dict", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "list", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.list", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}]}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "np_config.rigs.get_comp_id", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "str | None", "xref": null, "params": null}, "documentation": ["local computer properties ------------------------------------------------------------"]}, {"name": "np_config.rigs.get_rig_id", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "str | None", "xref": null, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "np_config.rigs.get_rig_idx", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "int | None", "xref": null, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "np_config.rigs.get_rig_config", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "idx_or_id", "type": {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "int | str", "xref": null, "params": null}]}, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "dict[Hashable, Any] | None", "xref": null, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Get the rig-specific config dict for the specified rig index or ID, fetched\nfrom ZooKeeper. If no index or ID is provided, returns the config dict for the\ncurrent rig, if running on an NP rig.\n\n```pycon\n>>> get_rig_config(1)['pretest_mouse']\n599657\n```\n"]}], "variables": [{"name": "np_config.rigs.logger", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "np_config.rigs.SERVER", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "np_config.rigs.get_comp_ids", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "np_config.rigs.get_rig_ids", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "np_config.rigs.get_cluster_ids", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "np_config.rigs.Rig", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "np_config.rigs.Rig.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "idx_or_id", "type": {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "int | str", "xref": null, "params": null}]}, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "np_config.rigs.Rig.__str__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "np_config.rigs.Rig.__repr__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "np_config.rigs.Rig.sync", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "np_config.rigs.Rig.mon", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "np_config.rigs.Rig.acq", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "np_config.rigs.Rig.stim", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project":